text.tspan: Change in number of published titles, 1470 to 1799
Illustrates the number of English and Latin titles published in England, and the German books printed in German, in
German speaking territories. A “title” is treated by the ESTC editors as an edition. The eight editions of Robinson
Crusoe published in 1719 create eight ESTC-entries.
